      "message": "It needs to listen to changes in `_shownFiles` rather than in `_files` because `_shownFiles` is the one that drives the DOM update (the expensive work).\n\nFor example, if, it hypothetically listened to `_files`, and then it\u0027s set to something like 10k file-paths, then we\u0027d only observe the timing for the first 200 of them -- and we wouldn\u0027t observe anything if the user clicks [Show All].\n\nSo, since this only works if it listens to the change that drives the UI update, it\u0027s in this `_computeFilesShown` method. Granted, it could go into a new observer of `_shownFiles`, but that seemed excessive.",
